    <section class="band section" id="standard" aria-labelledby="standard-title">
      <div class="wrap section-grid">
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="section-label">What Arky is</p>
          <h2 id="standard-title">A public protocol for accountable action.</h2>
          <p class="lead">A standard is adopted when independent systems can read the same artifacts, replay the same evidence, and reach the same result.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="definition reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 100ms">
          <p>A minimal public protocol that records who acted, with what evidence, under which policy, and what actually happened.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="band section" id="loop" aria-labelledby="loop-title">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-grid">
          <div class="reveal">
            <p class="section-label">Core loop</p>
            <h2 id="loop-title">Evidence to decision to receipt.</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="lead reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 100ms">Arky turns messy, real-world evidence into deterministic decisions and signed receipts that any rail can verify.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="protocol-grid" aria-label="Arky core loop">
          <article class="protocol-step reveal">
            <div class="step-index">01</div>
            <h3>TIM</h3>
            <p>Cryptographic evidence: who, what, when, signed and content-addressed.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="protocol-step reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 70ms">
            <div class="step-index">02</div>
            <h3>Notary</h3>
            <p>Witness time, order, and finality so evidence can be verified later.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="protocol-step reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 140ms">
            <div class="step-index">03</div>
            <h3>Kernel</h3>
            <p>Deterministic decisions under declared policy and assertions.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="protocol-step reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 210ms">
            <div class="step-index">04</div>
            <h3>Settlers</h3>
            <p>Execute verbs on banks, blockchains, or devices.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="protocol-step reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 280ms">
            <div class="step-index">05</div>
            <h3>Receipt</h3>
            <p>Signed outcome tied to the decision, rail, and anchors.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="band section" id="adopt" aria-labelledby="adopt-title">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-grid">
          <div class="reveal">
            <p class="section-label">Adoption path</p>
            <h2 id="adopt-title">Read the spec. Run the vectors. Ship conformance.</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 100ms">
            <p class="lead">The conversion is technical adoption, not a signup. Teams validate artifacts locally, compare behavior against vectors, then implement the core loop in their stack.</p>
            <p class="conversion">read spec <span>-&gt;</span> run vectors <span>-&gt;</span> ship implementation</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="path-grid">
          <article class="path-card reveal">
            <p class="claim">1 / SPEC</p>
            <h3>Read</h3>
            <p>Start with the normative core documents for TIM, Notary, Kernel, Settlers, and Policy Packs.</p>
            <a href="../specs/core/README.md">Open core specs</a>
          </article>

          <article class="path-card reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 90ms">
            <p class="claim">2 / VERIFY</p>
            <h3>Validate</h3>
            <p>Run the repository checks: JSON syntax, conformance verifier, Kernel schema checks, and link resolution.</p>
            <div class="terminal">
              <div class="terminal-head">
                <span>local conformance</span>
                <button class="copy-command" type="button" data-copy="bun install&#10;bun run validate">copy</button>
              </div>
              <pre><code>bun install
bun run validate</code></pre>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="path-card reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 180ms">
            <p class="claim">3 / IMPLEMENT</p>
            <h3>Build</h3>
            <p>Use the TypeScript and Rust reference packages as executable anchors for conformant behavior.</p>
            <a href="../packages/core/README.md">TypeScript</a>
            <a href="../packages/core-rs/README.md">Rust</a>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="band section" id="conformance" aria-labelledby="conformance-title">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-grid">
          <div class="reveal">
            <p class="section-label">Conformance</p>
            <h2 id="conformance-title">Vectors over vibes.</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="lead reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 100ms">Conformance is pass/fail, not marketing. A spec is Stable only once its vectors pass on two or more independent implementations. The TypeScript and Rust reference stacks pass the published vectors and are cross-checked byte-for-byte.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="conformance-grid">
          <article class="conformance-item reveal">
            <p class="claim">VECTORS</p>
            <h3>Executable checks</h3>
            <p>Validation recomputes content IDs, verifies signatures and witnesses, and executes canonicalization, Merkle, finality, and Settler vectors.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="conformance-item reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 90ms">
            <p class="claim">IMPLEMENTATIONS</p>
            <h3>Two stacks</h3>
            <p><code>@arky/core</code> and <code>arky-core</code> cover the TIM to Kernel to Settler loop across TypeScript and Rust.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="conformance-item reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 180ms">
            <p class="claim">STATUS</p>
            <h3>Implementing</h3>
            <p>Formal ratification to stable is pending; the core loop has L2 coverage and production-ready manifests.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

